{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_8c586b1f0e4f46108370c852","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t|version| |python| |license| |ci| |coverage|\n2\t\n3\t.. |version| image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/fabric\n4\t    :target: https://pypi.org/project/fabric/\n5\t    :alt: PyPI - Package Version\n6\t.. |python| image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/fabric\n7\t    :target: https://pypi.org/project/fabric/\n8\t    :alt: PyPI - Python Version\n9\t.. |license| image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/l/fabric\n10\t    :target: https://github.com/fabric/fabric/blob/main/LICENSE\n11\t    :alt: PyPI - License\n12\t.. |ci| image:: https://img.shields.io/circleci/build/github/fabric/fabric/main\n13\t    :target: https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/fabric/fabric\n14\t    :alt: CircleCI\n15\t.. |coverage| image:: https://img.shields.io/codecov/c/gh/fabric/fabric\n16\t    :target: https://app.codecov.io/gh/fabric/fabric\n17\t    :alt: Codecov\n18\t\n19\tWelcome to Fabric!\n20\t==================\n21\t\n22\tFabric is a high level Python (2.7, 3.4+) library designed to execute shell\n23\tcommands remotely over SSH, yielding useful Python objects in return. It builds\n24\ton top of `Invoke <https://pyinvoke.org>`_ (subprocess command execution and\n25\tcommand-line features) and `Paramiko <https://paramiko.org>`_ (SSH protocol\n26\timplementation), extending their APIs to complement one another and provide\n27\tadditional functionality.\n28\t\n29\tTo find out what's new in this version of Fabric, please see `the changelog\n30\t<https://fabfile.org/changelog.html#{}>`_.\n31\t\n32\tThe project maintainer keeps a `roadmap\n33\t<https://bitprophet.org/projects#roadmap>`_ on his website.\n34\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9485fbff-0532-4f53-ae2a-c630e896dc24","uuid":"bb1af543-db5d-4eba-a3ee-9e61dbd813ba","timestamp":"2026-04-08T20:55:29.701Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.rst","content":"|version| |python| |license| |ci| |coverage|\n\n.. |version| image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/fabric\n    :target: https://pypi.org/project/fabric/\n    :alt: PyPI - Package Version\n.. |python| image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/fabric\n    :target: https://pypi.org/project/fabric/\n    :alt: PyPI - Python Version\n.. |license| image:: https://img.shields.io/pypi/l/fabric\n    :target: https://github.com/fabric/fabric/blob/main/LICENSE\n    :alt: PyPI - License\n.. |ci| image:: https://img.shields.io/circleci/build/github/fabric/fabric/main\n    :target: https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/fabric/fabric\n    :alt: CircleCI\n.. |coverage| image:: https://img.shields.io/codecov/c/gh/fabric/fabric\n    :target: https://app.codecov.io/gh/fabric/fabric\n    :alt: Codecov\n\nWelcome to Fabric!\n==================\n\nFabric is a high level Python (2.7, 3.4+) library designed to execute shell\ncommands remotely over SSH, yielding useful Python objects in return. It builds\non top of `Invoke <https://pyinvoke.org>`_ (subprocess command execution and\ncommand-line features) and `Paramiko <https://paramiko.org>`_ (SSH protocol\nimplementation), extending their APIs to complement one another and provide\nadditional functionality.\n\nTo find out what's new in this version of Fabric, please see `the changelog\n<https://fabfile.org/changelog.html#{}>`_.\n\nThe project maintainer keeps a `roadmap\n<https://bitprophet.org/projects#roadmap>`_ on his website.\n","numLines":34,"startLine":1,"totalLines":34}}}
